      <p>As previously mentioned, <inline-formula id="IE225"><mml:math id="IM225" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="sans-serif">Seedability</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula> also estimates the number <italic toggle="yes">t</italic> of shared seeds, for an output <italic toggle="yes">k</italic> value, that can be found within an aligned pair of sequences. <xref rid="vbad108-T2" ref-type="table">Table 2</xref> shows the number of pairs of sequences out of 100 where <italic toggle="yes">t</italic> is within <inline-formula id="IE226"><mml:math id="IM226" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mo>±</mml:mo><mml:mn>10</mml:mn><mml:mo>%</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula> of the number of seeds in an optimal alignment. We set <italic toggle="yes">δ </italic>= 0 to evaluate how well <inline-formula id="IE227"><mml:math id="IM227" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="sans-serif">Seedability</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula> can perform this task.</p>
